        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 4:48PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Segundo, or 22 miles southwest of Trinidad, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Segundo and Weston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
